List of industrial parks or estates by land area:

Kizad Khalifa Industrial Zone, Abu Dhabi (Kizad), United Arab Emirates. When completed, the 418 square kilometres (103,000 acres) Kizad site will become one of the Middle East's largest industrial free-trade and non-free trade zones
Alberta's Industrial Heartland, Edmonton Capital Region, AB, Canada – 78,550 acres (318 km2) (planned use)
Rotterdam Harbour, Netherlands. It stretches for 40 kilometres (25 mi), and is 105 square kilometres (26,000 acres) large.
KAEC Industrial Valley, King Abdullah Economic City (KAEC), Saudi Arabia. The new logistics and manufacturing hub on the Red Sea and the new gateway to the GCC and East Africa, spreads over 55 square kilometres (14,000 acres). [1]
Nisku Industrial Park, Leduc County, AB, Canada. 2,044 hectares (20.44 km2; 7.89 sq mi) (over 400 businesses and more than 6,000 workers)
Cedar Crossing Industrial Park 15,000 acres (61 km2), in Houston, TX.
Tahoe-Reno Industrial Center 15,000 acres (61 km2), in Reno, NV.
TexAmericas Center, 12,000 acres, Texarkana MSA, Unincorporated Bowie County, Texas. Foreign Trade Zone #258 & HUB Zone. 36 miles of rail. 3msf of existing industrial space. 28 companies and 1000 employees.
MidAmerica Industrial Park 9,000 acres (36 km2), near Tusla, OK, located near Tulsa, OK.
Sri City Integrated Business City 7,500 acres, Andhra Pradesh, India.
Great Southwest Industrial Park 7,000 acres (28 km2), in Arlington, TX and Grand Prairie, TX
Butibori,Nagpur- 5,714 acres (23.12 km2) Five star industrial area(MIDC), Butibori,Nagpur,Maharastra(Largest in Asia in terms of area 23.12 km^2)
Burnside Industrial Park, Dartmouth, NS, Canada – 3,500 acres (14 km2)
North West Industrial SDA, Saskatoon, SK, Canada – 3,350 acres (13.6 km2)
Fort Custer Industrial Park, Battle Creek, MI, USA - 3,000 acres (12 km2)
Pureland Industrial Complex, Logan Township, NJ, United States – 3,000 acres (12 km2)
Trafford Park, Trafford, Greater Manchester, United Kingdom - 3,000 acres (12 km2)
CenterPoint Intermodal Center, Elwood, IL, USA – 2,050 acres (8.3 km2)
Wrexham Industrial Estate, Wrexham, United Kingdom – 1,359 acres (5.50 km2)
Eastman Business Park, Rochester, NY, USA - 1,200 acres (4.9 km2).
Ploiesti West Park, Ariceștii Rahtivani, Romania - 3 square kilometres (740 acres), largest industrial park in South East Europe
Caracol Industrial Park, Caracol, Haiti – 600 acres (2.4 km2)
Slough Trading Estate, Slough, United Kingdom – 600 acres (2.4 km2)}
Green Valley Industrial Park, Naco, Santa Barbara, Honduras – 500 acres (2.0 km2)
Chittagong Export Processing Zone, Chittagong, Bangladesh - 453 acres (1.83 km2)
Electronics City, Bangalore, India (1978) – 330 acres (1.3 km2)
